			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Chaosmage,
<br />

<br />
How about.. oh, NOT. Get over yourself. You can use the term 'Conjurer' to mean that we can summon any damn thing we want to. Why can't we summon Elemental armor? Because it's no fun if it's handed to you on a plate, that's why. Why can't we summon reagents for whatever we want? Platinum? Oh, wait. It's because it defeats the purpose of the damn game.
<br />

<br />
This is not D&D. At best, it is D&D-<span style="font-style: italic">like</span>. It has magic, casters, warriors and clerics. That's pretty much where it ends. After that, the spell selections, the things you can do, the lore, the world, the breakdown of classes, the abilities, the power ratings, the experience tables... it's way off the D&D mark. Don't bring it up. You can use it as a comparison, but never ever attempt to justify something in EQ by it's presence in another <span style="font-style: italic">like</span> game.
<br />

<br />
In the case of Everquest, it makes sense for knights (in history, in lore, etc) to have the ability to 'call' to a mount of theirs. Yes, we could have every class in the game summon up their mount. Clerics their godly steed, mages summon a special riding pet, wizards their mount, druids ride wolves, etc etc etc. Why won't that happen? Here, it's simple.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">Because there is no valid point in the game beyond 'Ooo, that's neat' to giving everyone a mount with AAs.</span>
<br />

<br />
If Magicians get one, why not wizards? Why not warriors? Rangers? Shaman and Enchanters? Hell, Enchanters could charm any mob the wanted to carry them. <span style="font-weight: bold">Why Not?</span> Because there is no damn good reason that every class has a mount. There are pleanty of reasons not to, but almost none that anyone has bothered to come up with here as to why we deserve, need, have to have, or justify a mount that we can summon.
<br />

<br />
Put up or shut up. What would make a magician stand out enough in the field of 'ridden mounts' to point to a unique ability to call a mount to us?</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
